<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">January Continued 1808</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">comes to see if he can obtain any other young men of the Grand Chefre's band (who are to come to the Fort in this Moon) to go to the Beaver Country<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e has now given 60 Skins in furrs Since the Fall including his Coatings &#8211; which for a man who is lame in arm is not I hope altogether amiss &#8211; notwithstanding that some him out to be a <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Spoiled</span> &#8211; if all spoiled <span class="DelHand-author">of</span> Indians of the Posts where such <span style="text-decoration:underline;">accomplished</span> Gentlemen Winter were to work as well in proportion &#8211; Would not these Critics have made better returns last year<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I Kept his majesty's Scullion to supply the Place of the Gaucher<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[P]</span>retty good weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 2<sup>nd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off the above Indians<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Capot Rouge is to wait a month &amp; no longer<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday 3<sup>rd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Croup de Chien brought 55 Hares to day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Sun<sup>y</sup> 4<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent away again the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Dog's</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Rump</span> to his Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mon<sup>y</sup> 5<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Tues<sup>y</sup> 6<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[N]</span>othing particular<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fa-t-g Father brought 20 Hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off immediately, his wife is at home<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Wednes<sup>y</sup> 7<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  No news<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The men Chop &amp; draw wood<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thurs<sup>y</sup> 8<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Jollibois with two Indians Came from Grand Chefre<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>his last sends me word that he is yet in quest of the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Dahotinnais</span> and that as he will not be able to comply with my request of last Fall of going above the Fort towards the River des <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Couteau</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Rouges</span> in quest of Beaver &#8211; that he will Trench Beaver behind the Old Rocky Mo<sup>n</sup> Fort where he has discovered a few B<sup>r</sup> Lodges<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Jollibois</span> tells me the same, i.e. that the whole band intimated the very same Story<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The two fellow Travellers of Jollibois brought 21 Skins in furrs &amp; 2 in Prov<sup>ns</sup> Grand Chefre Sent me 3½ Skins of Fat &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Mufles</span> or rather noses<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 9<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Allowed my lately arrived guests to remain here to day on account of the bad weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday 10<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off Jollibois &amp; his Companions to Resume his Station in land<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[D]</span>esired him to do his utmost endeavors to encourage his band work every Beaver they might come across<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Very bad weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sun<sup>y</sup> 11<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Monday 12<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[N]</span>othing Strange worth mentioning<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup>13<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  One of the Hare Hunters brought 38 Hares to day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span> Dog's rump has <span style="text-decoration:underline;">shrunk</span> &#8211; takes no more Hares being extremely unwell<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednes<sup>y</sup> 14<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off the above again to his Collets &#8211; for I believe he will make a pretty good <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Hangman</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fine weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thurs<sup>y</sup> 15<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[N]</span>othing occured deserving of Notice<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[21]</span></p>

